line_1: (Nor, like those pairs whom sentiment unites,
line_2: Feel they the fervour of the mind's delights;)

line_1: The Nations say Amen, and all of course Unites.
Their climes are distant, tho' one cause unites
line_2: The lairds of Scotland, and the Cornish knights.

line_1: Fancy with Vigor in his Stile unites.
line_2: Than Dennis none with greater Judgment writes,
